1
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:52,093
Why are you in such a hurry?

2
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:54,595
Why don't you wait for Jamie
so you can go to school together?

3
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:57,057
I still have a lot to do.
I need to go ahead.

4
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:01,770
Please, come in.

5
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,396
And introduce yourself.

6
00:01:05,982 --> 00:01:06,982
Al?

7
00:01:08,026 --> 00:01:09,359
Good morning, everyone.

8
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:10,694
I'm Alistair Ravena.

9
00:01:10,695 --> 00:01:12,321
The Q.E.D. Club members are here.

10
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:13,322
Alright, hold on.

11
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:19,411
Welcome.

12
00:01:19,913 --> 00:01:20,830
I've been expecting you.

13
00:01:20,831 --> 00:01:23,833
Actually, I'm pleased to finally meet you
face-to-face, Ms. Lorelei.

14
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:25,251
Something strange is happening.

15
00:01:26,044 --> 00:01:27,628
The situation is weird.

16
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:29,464
Even if she doesn’t show herself to us,

17
00:01:29,798 --> 00:01:34,260
she still finds ways
to submit poems for our portfolio.

18
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:37,097
<i>Me and you, everything is tragedy.</i>

19
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:40,266
What makes you think it's an SOS message?

20
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:43,478
At first glance,
it looks like an ordinary poem.

21
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:46,313
And it could've looked like
your writer sent it by mistake.

22
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:47,731
But the truth is, she didn't.

23
00:01:47,732 --> 00:01:50,067
Actually, I feel like
I was really with Loki earlier

24
00:01:50,068 --> 00:01:52,362
with how quick you were able
to decipher that code.

25
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:55,948
The only difference
is you genuinely care about the victim.

26
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:57,509
Are you really going to pick that lock?

27
00:01:57,575 --> 00:01:58,201
Yes.

28
00:01:58,535 --> 00:02:01,287
Lori, are we about to do
something illegal? Huh?

29
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:03,039
What if someone sees us?

30
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:05,833
Then we'll be accused of trespassing.

31
00:02:05,834 --> 00:02:07,919
You just threw it away, huh?

32
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:11,631
If you won’t let me go, just kill me!

33
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,883
- Help!
- There, there.

34
00:02:15,176 --> 00:02:16,219
Whatever!

35
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:18,972
I don't want this anymore!

36
00:02:19,764 --> 00:02:21,766
- You shameless bastards!
- Tie him, tie him!

37
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:23,017
Just wait!

38
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:25,271
- I’m reporting you to the police!
- Tie him tight!

39
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:27,146
You should be the one preparing for us!

40
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,731
After what you did to Camille.

41
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:30,358
I kicked like that.

42
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:32,777
- I don’t know about you.
- You really are something.

43
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:33,777
Anytime.

44
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:39,116
Actually, he helped me solve
a case earlier,

45
00:02:39,117 --> 00:02:41,077
so that’s where we came from.

46
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:43,288
Interesting!

47
00:02:43,872 --> 00:02:47,041
Care to update me
before the rest of our blog readers?

48
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:50,879
Welcome to the Q.E.D. Club.

49
00:03:15,111 --> 00:03:16,237
Moria...

50
00:03:19,824 --> 00:03:23,203
<i>Can you describe his voice?</i>

51
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,788
<i>Cold and deep.</i>

52
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,166
- You’ll get goosebumps when you hear it.
- Moriarty.

53
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:33,379
<i>I think the person
they were talking to was a man.</i>

54
00:03:34,422 --> 00:03:36,049
<i>There was something off about him.</i>

55
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:40,553
<i>He had a lollipop in his mouth that time.</i>

56
00:03:46,851 --> 00:03:49,020
<i>A big sin...</i>

57
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:51,648
<i>a wrong committed against him.</i>

58
00:04:00,114 --> 00:04:02,951
<i>I’m just a pawn on his chessboard.</i>

59
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,786
<i>All of their requests...</i>

60
00:04:05,620 --> 00:04:07,914
<i>we'll pass to Moriarty.</i>

61
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:12,043
<i>What would an officer be doing</i>

62
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:15,630
<i>in the place where you supposedly
kidnapped yourself?</i>

63
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:25,014
<i>It’s a pleasure
to finally meet you in person.</i>

64
00:04:25,431 --> 00:04:27,350
I am Moriarty.

65
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:15,815
Is that for your Humanities class?

66
00:05:16,524 --> 00:05:19,152
This is Moriarty's spider web
of conspiracy.

67
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:25,616
So you're saying,
Stein a.k.a. Moriarty,

68
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:29,370
is a spider?

69
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:33,166
"A spider that sits motionless

70
00:05:33,583 --> 00:05:35,877
at the center of this bloody web."

71
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:41,174
If I were to borrow
Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's words.

72
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,010
You're so serious.

73
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,440
Just kidding.

74
00:05:48,052 --> 00:05:49,303
But all jokes aside,

75
00:05:50,216 --> 00:05:52,343
what Stein’s doing isn’t funny.

76
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:56,773
But this one...

77
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,149
we have no proof

78
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:02,612
that Stein is connected
to the murders plotted by Moriarty.

79
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:07,283
But we can get that
from the people connected to him.

80
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:10,577
May I?

81
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:12,871
Be my guest.

82
00:06:32,058 --> 00:06:34,060
If three of them are dead,

83
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:36,229
and one’s a convict,

84
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:39,023
and we still don’t know
who Lollipop Guy is,

85
00:06:39,482 --> 00:06:42,151
that means our closest link to Moriarty

86
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:44,028
is Officer Montreal.

87
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:47,698
Because he’s the one
I saw calling Moriarty’s number.

88
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:49,617
My guess is,

89
00:06:49,909 --> 00:06:53,871
he’s the one who can give us
the evidence we need to convict Stein.

90
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:56,790
Precisely.

91
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:03,714
So, should we start an operation
to gather evidence?

92
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:08,302
Or do we just leave it to chance

93
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,930
and wait until we encounter him on a case?

94
00:07:12,306 --> 00:07:13,433
My concern is…

95
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,394
is this the right thread to follow?

96
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:19,021
Is it really this simple?

97
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:24,277
Because what if Stein
is not the real Moriarty?

98
00:07:28,605 --> 00:07:30,274
<i>♪ Shadows. ♪</i>

99
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:33,902
<i>♪ In the dark are crawling. ♪</i>

100
00:07:34,611 --> 00:07:38,656
<i>♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪</i>

101
00:07:38,657 --> 00:07:42,202
<i>♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪</i>

102
00:07:43,162 --> 00:07:46,748
<i>♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪</i>

103
00:07:46,749 --> 00:07:49,917
<i>♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪</i>

104
00:07:49,918 --> 00:07:52,879
<i>♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪</i>

105
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:57,384
<i>♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪</i>

106
00:07:58,761 --> 00:08:00,888
<i>♪ Heed the warnings. ♪</i>

107
00:08:02,139 --> 00:08:04,516
<i>♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪</i>

108
00:08:05,601 --> 00:08:09,271
<i>♪ For this world ♪</i>

109
00:08:09,938 --> 00:08:12,565
<i>♪ is not what you imagined. ♪</i>

110
00:08:12,566 --> 00:08:15,027
<i>♪ Heed the warnings. ♪</i>

111
00:08:16,028 --> 00:08:18,155
<i>♪ Open up your eyes. ♪</i>

112
00:08:19,448 --> 00:08:22,993
<i>♪ For this world ♪</i>

113
00:08:23,702 --> 00:08:26,245
<i>♪ is not what you imagined. ♪</i>

114
00:08:26,246 --> 00:08:31,085
<i>♪ Heed the warnings. ♪</i>

115
00:08:35,851 --> 00:08:37,520
But he admitted it, didn’t he?

116
00:08:38,173 --> 00:08:39,508
That’s why you got mad.

117
00:08:40,578 --> 00:08:42,621
It was wrong of me
to let myself go like that.

118
00:08:44,820 --> 00:08:45,987
But the point is…

119
00:08:46,428 --> 00:08:48,763
what if he's just like that officer?

120
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:53,082
What if he's only a proxy
sent by the real one

121
00:08:53,349 --> 00:08:55,225
to play mind games with us?

122
00:08:56,445 --> 00:08:57,863
That's possible.

123
00:08:58,822 --> 00:09:02,409
But as long as there is no new evidence
to prove otherwise,

124
00:09:02,948 --> 00:09:04,533
I'm gonna take his word for it,

125
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:06,606
that he really is Moriarty.

126
00:09:12,013 --> 00:09:13,277
Do you want more coffee?

127
00:09:15,535 --> 00:09:16,828
I can make you another cup.

128
00:09:18,390 --> 00:09:20,225
I don’t think we have time
for a second cup.

129
00:09:23,488 --> 00:09:25,281
You need to dress up, don’t you?

130
00:09:26,394 --> 00:09:27,394
Dress up?

131
00:09:27,675 --> 00:09:29,552
For what exactly?

132
00:09:30,452 --> 00:09:31,995
You’ve forgotten about our date.

133
00:09:32,371 --> 00:09:33,371
Date?

134
00:09:35,532 --> 00:09:38,201
<i>Wait, Lorelei, are you free this weekend?</i>

135
00:09:39,558 --> 00:09:41,977
I don’t have anything planned
this weekend yet.

136
00:09:42,687 --> 00:09:43,687
Why?

137
00:09:44,624 --> 00:09:46,042
<i>I’d like to invite you on a date.</i>

138
00:09:46,912 --> 00:09:47,912
Huh?

139
00:09:50,056 --> 00:09:51,056
Wait. Wait.

140
00:09:51,315 --> 00:09:52,608
I thought that was a joke.

141
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:56,660
And why would you even
go out with me?

142
00:09:56,771 --> 00:10:00,870
Jamie’s there, or whoever. Why me...

143
00:10:00,902 --> 00:10:02,445
It’s not a romantic date.

144
00:10:03,919 --> 00:10:05,961
- Oh...
- It’s more like a…

145
00:10:05,986 --> 00:10:06,695
Sorry.

146
00:10:06,924 --> 00:10:08,509
It’s more of a case consultation.

147
00:10:09,279 --> 00:10:10,523
But you’re still suspended, right?

148
00:10:10,548 --> 00:10:11,716
But in a different school.

149
00:10:12,203 --> 00:10:14,163
Ah… I see.

150
00:10:15,016 --> 00:10:17,310
Okay. Well, in that case…

151
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:18,690
count me in!

152
00:10:19,709 --> 00:10:22,462
Are we including Jamie or Al?

153
00:10:22,689 --> 00:10:24,691
Since he's a new member of Q.E.D. Club.

154
00:10:25,404 --> 00:10:26,655
She’s unavailable.

155
00:10:27,913 --> 00:10:30,666
But you can ask your childhood friend
to tag along.

156
00:10:31,807 --> 00:10:33,392
Okay. I’ll do that.

157
00:10:42,049 --> 00:10:44,193
Lori, is everything okay?

158
00:10:44,218 --> 00:10:45,218
Of course!

159
00:10:45,678 --> 00:10:48,639
Loki just wants to know
if you want to tag along with us

160
00:10:48,664 --> 00:10:50,999
to a school we’re going to today.

161
00:10:51,631 --> 00:10:55,162
Someone requested
his assistance on a case,

162
00:10:55,187 --> 00:10:57,122
and we’re about to investigate it.

163
00:10:57,662 --> 00:11:01,166
I would love to,
but I’m heading back to Manila now.

164
00:11:01,502 --> 00:11:03,003
<i>I’ll make it up to you and Loki.</i>

165
00:11:03,338 --> 00:11:04,338
I see.

166
00:11:04,547 --> 00:11:07,299
That’s unfortunate.
It was only confirmed now.

167
00:11:07,713 --> 00:11:08,755
<i>You know…</i>

168
00:11:08,780 --> 00:11:10,573
if I can help you with anything,

169
00:11:11,332 --> 00:11:13,209
just call me right away, okay?

170
00:11:14,098 --> 00:11:15,224
Honestly…

171
00:11:15,663 --> 00:11:18,207
I’d rather be solving cases with you.

172
00:11:19,061 --> 00:11:20,604
But I can’t.

173
00:11:21,175 --> 00:11:24,845
I don’t really want to do
what they’re making me do in Manila.

174
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:28,699
Okay. I’ll tell Loki you’ll be in touch.

175
00:11:29,070 --> 00:11:30,778
Take care on your trip, okay?

176
00:11:30,803 --> 00:11:31,387
<i>Okay.</i>

177
00:11:31,412 --> 00:11:37,654
Take care too. Just call me
if you need anything, Lori, okay?

178
00:11:38,471 --> 00:11:39,471
Bye.

179
00:11:43,407 --> 00:11:45,117
Looks like it’s just the two of us again.

180
00:12:09,210 --> 00:12:11,755
I was never fond of anything
that defies logic.

181
00:12:12,412 --> 00:12:13,824
But I need to read it

182
00:12:13,849 --> 00:12:17,060
so I can understand
the other elements of this case.

183
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:21,084
Are you familiar with chain messages?

184
00:12:22,755 --> 00:12:25,067
Those stupid messages that say
you'll be hit with bad luck

185
00:12:25,068 --> 00:12:28,193
if you won't forward it
to a certain number of people?

186
00:12:30,685 --> 00:12:31,685
Yeah.

187
00:12:32,374 --> 00:12:36,128
I remember, that used to be
popular in my school back then.

188
00:12:37,421 --> 00:12:40,633
What’s the connection to Wizardly?

189
00:12:42,977 --> 00:12:46,189
Well, at the school we’re going to,

190
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:51,312
there’s a fan group dedicated to the lore
of this young adult fiction work.

191
00:12:52,894 --> 00:12:55,272
And recently,

192
00:12:55,794 --> 00:12:58,421
two members of the club were found dead

193
00:12:58,963 --> 00:13:01,466
after receiving a mysterious text message.

194
00:13:01,924 --> 00:13:04,259
Message? What message?

195
00:13:05,014 --> 00:13:06,098
Havre k'davra.

196
00:13:06,669 --> 00:13:07,669
Huh?

197
00:13:08,123 --> 00:13:10,334
That spell was part of the chain message

198
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:14,168
received by the two victims
before their death.

199
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:18,026
Died because of a chain message?

200
00:13:18,936 --> 00:13:22,303
Wait, what’s the meaning of "havre..."

201
00:13:22,328 --> 00:13:23,412
Havre k'davra!

202
00:13:24,792 --> 00:13:25,835
According to the book,

203
00:13:26,032 --> 00:13:30,662
that spell causes an instantaneous
painless death to the target.

204
00:13:32,293 --> 00:13:36,297
Well, I can’t read all of this right now.

205
00:13:37,514 --> 00:13:40,225
Too bad Jamie’s not here.

206
00:13:40,786 --> 00:13:43,623
Her photographic memory would’ve helped.

207
00:13:45,311 --> 00:13:46,395
And the other day...

208
00:13:47,856 --> 00:13:51,026
you were surprised to hear
that Jamie slept in my room.

209
00:13:52,525 --> 00:13:53,525
In my bed.

210
00:13:55,065 --> 00:13:56,275
Did that bother you?

211
00:14:02,052 --> 00:14:03,470
Loki!

212
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,023
- Stop it!
- Jamie!

213
00:14:09,604 --> 00:14:10,813
Come on.

214
00:14:15,668 --> 00:14:16,668
No!

215
00:14:17,672 --> 00:14:19,174
Why would that bother me?

216
00:14:20,482 --> 00:14:22,234
Well, you’ve got nothing to worry about.

217
00:14:23,391 --> 00:14:25,142
Nothing happened between me and Jamie.

218
00:14:27,385 --> 00:14:30,346
I’ve built a wall of pillows
between us when we slept.

219
00:15:22,855 --> 00:15:25,983
My acquaintance is a tech genius
and a brilliant inventor.

220
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:28,626
He could’ve made money
from his inventions,

221
00:15:28,627 --> 00:15:32,981
but he chose not to sell his patents.

222
00:15:33,342 --> 00:15:35,135
What are his inventions?

223
00:15:37,119 --> 00:15:38,745
Remember that stun pen I gave you?

224
00:15:39,312 --> 00:15:40,312
He made that one.

225
00:15:40,953 --> 00:15:42,474
Well, I can’t wait to finally meet him.

226
00:15:42,499 --> 00:15:44,543
What’s your business here, ma’am? Sir?

227
00:15:45,476 --> 00:15:47,100
Offices are closed today. It's Saturday.

228
00:15:47,148 --> 00:15:50,401
Sir! They’re with me! Let them in!

229
00:15:51,890 --> 00:15:54,392
Hi! Hi! Thanks for coming today, Loki.

230
00:15:54,417 --> 00:15:56,002
So you must be Lorelei?

231
00:15:56,863 --> 00:15:58,217
I'm Herschel Aguirre.

232
00:15:58,242 --> 00:16:00,133
It's nice to finally meet
the creator of the stun pen!

233
00:16:00,592 --> 00:16:03,345
I had someone I know who
is good at inventions do it.

234
00:16:03,979 --> 00:16:06,968
It's a stunning device disguised as a pen
that you can bring anywhere.

235
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,565
Stun pen? Ah...

236
00:16:16,396 --> 00:16:18,231
I hope you’re not using it for pranks.

237
00:16:19,891 --> 00:16:22,477
Seems you’re like the boss
around here, huh, Hershey?

238
00:16:22,948 --> 00:16:24,533
He can never remember my name.

239
00:16:24,909 --> 00:16:26,201
I gave up on that.

240
00:16:27,755 --> 00:16:28,965
So, shall we?

241
00:16:29,858 --> 00:16:30,858
Let's go.

242
00:16:36,780 --> 00:16:38,317
Come on, guys. This is our playground.

243
00:16:38,351 --> 00:16:40,125
It's exactly where we do everything.

244
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:41,898
This is our lab, as you can see.

245
00:16:43,602 --> 00:16:44,602
Sorry! Sorry!

246
00:16:44,929 --> 00:16:50,092
I forgot the oven’s voltage
isn’t compatible with our outlet.

247
00:16:50,117 --> 00:16:53,623
I was just about to heat up
the pizza I bought for our guest.

248
00:16:53,648 --> 00:16:55,202
Leona! Did you forget that...

249
00:16:55,227 --> 00:16:56,562
Help me out here!

250
00:16:56,955 --> 00:16:57,955
Move!

251
00:16:59,041 --> 00:17:01,542
Did you forget it's not an ordinary oven?

252
00:17:01,543 --> 00:17:02,544
Did you forget?

253
00:17:02,878 --> 00:17:05,130
Safety is priority number one.

254
00:17:05,756 --> 00:17:08,008
Second, wear your gloves and your gown.

255
00:17:10,177 --> 00:17:12,846
Everyone, meet my assistant, Leona Divino.

256
00:17:13,847 --> 00:17:15,056
She helped me develop the stun pen.

257
00:17:15,057 --> 00:17:16,515
Hi! Nice to meet you.

258
00:17:16,516 --> 00:17:17,935
Hi. Nice to meet you!

259
00:17:18,785 --> 00:17:19,828
Come on. Come on.

260
00:17:20,016 --> 00:17:24,521
Leona is a member of the Wizardly Club
that... What was it again?

261
00:17:24,983 --> 00:17:25,901
Fellowship of the Wand.

262
00:17:25,902 --> 00:17:27,044
Fellowship of the Wand!

263
00:17:27,069 --> 00:17:28,736
My precious club.

264
00:17:28,737 --> 00:17:30,781
Herschel, wrong reference.

265
00:17:31,114 --> 00:17:32,282
Tomato, tomato.

266
00:17:33,784 --> 00:17:36,535
Two members were found unalive,
but Leona can tell you more about it.

267
00:17:36,536 --> 00:17:37,971
Yeah! Come with us!

268
00:17:38,096 --> 00:17:39,096
Come.

269
00:17:41,445 --> 00:17:43,822
Herschel! Hey! Come here!

270
00:17:47,422 --> 00:17:48,923
The member who were found dead

271
00:17:48,924 --> 00:17:52,260
are Godfrey Griffin and Sylvester Salazar.

272
00:17:52,809 --> 00:17:55,937
Both are founding members
of Fellowship of the Wand.

273
00:17:57,414 --> 00:18:00,041
This is Godfrey,
the one with the red scarf.

274
00:18:05,232 --> 00:18:09,277
This happened after the general assembly,
around 6:00 p.m.

275
00:18:15,742 --> 00:18:18,036
I was there when it happened to Sylvester.

276
00:18:18,787 --> 00:18:21,914
The meeting
for the club acquaintance party

277
00:18:21,915 --> 00:18:23,875
that will be held
later this afternoon just ended.

278
00:18:24,376 --> 00:18:26,837
Oh, here. Hold on. Let me show you, guys.

279
00:18:27,873 --> 00:18:32,252
I’m also with Syvester,
the one wearing a green scarf at the back.

280
00:19:01,705 --> 00:19:04,415
Some members of the Fellowship think that

281
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:08,170
the message the contains the Havre K’davra
killed two founders.

282
00:19:08,670 --> 00:19:10,881
But that’s… that’s impossible, right?

283
00:19:11,423 --> 00:19:13,550
There’s no way a message can kill.

284
00:19:14,092 --> 00:19:16,470
Huh? How did that happen? Magic?

285
00:19:18,263 --> 00:19:19,890
There’s no such thing as magic.

286
00:19:20,724 --> 00:19:23,685
There may be a logical explanation
for the deaths of the two founders.

287
00:19:24,686 --> 00:19:27,064
And we will get to the bottom of this.

288
00:19:28,136 --> 00:19:31,056
Lorelei and I would be glad
to take on this case.

289
00:19:38,575 --> 00:19:39,576
Look.

290
00:19:41,052 --> 00:19:43,888
- You can see Sylvester there...
- I see.

291
00:19:56,217 --> 00:19:57,259
Pressure.

292
00:19:57,776 --> 00:19:58,776
Click.

293
00:19:59,407 --> 00:20:00,407
Okay.

294
00:20:42,472 --> 00:20:45,567
<i>It's been weeks
since I personally solved a case.</i>

295
00:20:46,164 --> 00:20:49,042
<i>Solving cases really makes
my overall wellness better.</i>

296
00:20:50,027 --> 00:20:52,676
<i>I'm more excited to know
who's the real killer.</i>

297
00:21:35,709 --> 00:21:38,337
Hey! Coffee! Here.

298
00:21:39,533 --> 00:21:40,618
Hold on.

299
00:21:56,463 --> 00:21:58,089
Here. Coffee.

300
00:21:58,465 --> 00:21:59,632
Thanks!

301
00:21:59,866 --> 00:22:03,192
Do you think Loki will be stuck
in the security office for long?

302
00:22:03,987 --> 00:22:07,782
I'm not sure, but I think
they're reviewing a lot of footage.

303
00:22:07,807 --> 00:22:09,935
Why? Do you still need anything?

304
00:22:10,249 --> 00:22:11,667
So far, nothing yet.

305
00:22:12,312 --> 00:22:14,730
I’ll study this autopsy report first.

306
00:22:14,731 --> 00:22:15,565
Okay.

307
00:22:15,607 --> 00:22:18,026
Well, is it okay
if I leave you again for a bit?

308
00:22:18,235 --> 00:22:20,778
I have to go 'cause I have to pick up
some things

309
00:22:20,779 --> 00:22:22,529
for the acquaintance party later.

310
00:22:22,661 --> 00:22:24,245
Yeah, sure. No worries.

311
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:25,647
Okay! Enjoy your coffee.

312
00:22:41,383 --> 00:22:42,384
Hello, Al!

313
00:22:44,135 --> 00:22:45,387
<i>Is the signal okay now?</i>

314
00:22:45,824 --> 00:22:47,325
Can you hear me, Al?

315
00:22:47,685 --> 00:22:49,061
<i>Yes. Loud and clear, Lori.</i>

316
00:22:49,366 --> 00:22:50,909
I got your message about the case.

317
00:22:51,082 --> 00:22:53,251
I can’t reply right away
’cause I’m driving.

318
00:22:53,645 --> 00:22:54,729
Are you busy?

319
00:22:55,021 --> 00:22:57,564
I can call later
if now is not a good time.

320
00:22:57,565 --> 00:22:59,484
No. It’s fine. I don’t mind.

321
00:23:00,026 --> 00:23:02,320
It’s better to have someone with you
while you’re driving.

322
00:23:02,988 --> 00:23:04,239
<i>What’s the cause of death?</i>

323
00:23:04,781 --> 00:23:07,033
Well, according to the report...

324
00:23:07,593 --> 00:23:12,764
the cause of death is asphyxia
due to neuromuscular blockade

325
00:23:12,789 --> 00:23:15,292
caused by the poison curare.

326
00:23:15,667 --> 00:23:19,878
It says here that curare
is a type of poison that causes paralysis,

327
00:23:19,879 --> 00:23:22,464
which then leads to asphyxiation

328
00:23:22,465 --> 00:23:24,842
due to the victim’s inability

329
00:23:24,843 --> 00:23:26,761
to contract the respiratory muscles.

330
00:23:27,262 --> 00:23:28,638
<i>According to the autopsy,</i>

331
00:23:28,805 --> 00:23:31,599
<i>a puncture wound was found
in the victim’s nape.</i>

332
00:23:33,685 --> 00:23:34,686
Curare...

333
00:23:35,395 --> 00:23:38,148
So someone injected curare
into the victim?

334
00:23:39,316 --> 00:23:43,152
Or maybe someone stabbed them
with a needle laced with curare?

335
00:23:43,153 --> 00:23:44,195
That’s possible too.

336
00:23:44,654 --> 00:23:47,282
<i>But we already saw
some of the CCTV footage.</i>

337
00:23:47,615 --> 00:23:50,285
The victim was alone before he collapsed.

338
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,495
No one even approached him.

339
00:23:53,121 --> 00:23:57,709
Lori, I’m about to lose signal,
but just message me.

340
00:23:58,209 --> 00:24:00,170
I’ll call right after this, okay?

341
00:24:00,712 --> 00:24:03,965
Yeah, of course!
No problem, Al. Drive safe, okay?

342
00:24:08,345 --> 00:24:10,138
Hey! You’re already here.

343
00:24:10,513 --> 00:24:11,513
How’s it going?

344
00:24:11,681 --> 00:24:15,477
Did you find anything on the CCTV footage?

345
00:24:18,229 --> 00:24:19,229
Nothing.

346
00:24:20,231 --> 00:24:24,277
Even the phone number used
in the chain message can’t be tracked.

347
00:24:25,695 --> 00:24:27,405
What does the autopsy say?

348
00:24:27,739 --> 00:24:31,283
Well, it says here,
the cause of death is asphyxia

349
00:24:31,284 --> 00:24:35,205
caused by neuromuscular blockade
caused by the poison curare.

350
00:24:35,580 --> 00:24:40,292
What I still can’t figure out, though,
is how it was injected into the victims

351
00:24:40,293 --> 00:24:42,212
when no one even came near them?

352
00:24:44,172 --> 00:24:45,172
Have a look?

353
00:24:49,761 --> 00:24:51,721
This reminds me of a similar case.

354
00:24:53,181 --> 00:24:56,351
Do you remember the culprit
in Chemistry Lab Case?

355
00:24:56,810 --> 00:24:59,020
Yes, of course! Genesis Cabangon.

356
00:24:59,771 --> 00:25:00,939
Genesis Cabangon.

357
00:25:01,523 --> 00:25:04,442
He too was poisoned,
just like what happened here.

358
00:25:05,610 --> 00:25:07,070
He was also pricked in the nape.

359
00:25:07,946 --> 00:25:09,738
<i>According to the autopsy report,</i>

360
00:25:09,739 --> 00:25:12,742
<i>a broken needle tip
was found lodged in his nape.</i>

361
00:25:13,159 --> 00:25:17,580
A fast-acting paralytic
was detected in this area.

362
00:25:19,332 --> 00:25:20,332
Poison.

363
00:25:20,583 --> 00:25:22,335
John, John.

364
00:25:23,044 --> 00:25:24,879
John! John!

365
00:25:26,506 --> 00:25:30,051
We both know someone
who employs a similar modus.

366
00:25:31,136 --> 00:25:32,137
Moriarty?

367
00:25:33,096 --> 00:25:35,598
But Stein is still unconscious.

368
00:25:36,266 --> 00:25:40,770
Are you saying that Chivalry College
has their very own Moriarty?

369
00:25:42,355 --> 00:25:43,731
It’s too early to tell.

370
00:25:44,524 --> 00:25:45,984
We need more information.

371
00:25:46,860 --> 00:25:49,404
There are no students
we can ask right now.

372
00:25:49,737 --> 00:25:54,116
But the Fellowship of the Wand
is having a grand acquaintance party

373
00:25:54,117 --> 00:25:55,493
for the new members.

374
00:25:56,411 --> 00:25:58,163
Here you go!

375
00:25:58,455 --> 00:26:00,789
It’s a members-only event later,

376
00:26:00,790 --> 00:26:02,791
and members need to get dressed to fit in.

377
00:26:02,792 --> 00:26:03,960
- There you go.
- Here.

378
00:26:04,544 --> 00:26:05,544
Thanks.

379
00:26:06,796 --> 00:26:08,298
Are these hand-me-downs?

380
00:26:08,715 --> 00:26:11,943
Is this a scarf or a dish towel?

381
00:26:11,968 --> 00:26:12,968
Loki!

382
00:26:13,011 --> 00:26:15,388
Don’t worry, Loki. It’s all brand-new.

383
00:26:15,562 --> 00:26:17,856
But that’s how it is.

384
00:26:18,523 --> 00:26:21,067
They bought it from a supplier.

385
00:26:21,269 --> 00:26:23,020
It’s strange...

386
00:26:23,215 --> 00:26:27,344
their membership fees
and miscellaneous expenses are so high.

387
00:26:27,442 --> 00:26:29,611
But look at the items.

388
00:26:29,961 --> 00:26:31,671
They’re not worth the price.

389
00:26:31,696 --> 00:26:33,280
Substandard.

390
00:26:33,281 --> 00:26:36,743
Maybe that’s why
some Wiz-heads don’t join.

391
00:26:38,244 --> 00:26:41,998
Maybe the officers are getting kickbacks
from the membership fees?

392
00:26:42,582 --> 00:26:46,711
So that’s why
they’re using cheap suppliers?

393
00:26:47,462 --> 00:26:49,547
Maybe we should ask the members?

394
00:26:50,179 --> 00:26:53,306
Don’t look at me!
I’m not a fan of fantasy series.

395
00:26:53,331 --> 00:26:55,375
But they needed my services, so I obliged.

396
00:26:56,404 --> 00:26:58,406
Wait, let me demonstrate! Come here!

397
00:26:58,540 --> 00:26:59,540
Follow.

398
00:27:06,076 --> 00:27:07,076
Found it!

399
00:27:13,821 --> 00:27:16,949
Leona, my dear,
can you kindly close off the lights?

400
00:27:17,152 --> 00:27:18,737
Of course. Hold on.

401
00:27:23,046 --> 00:27:24,089
Ilumino!

402
00:27:26,933 --> 00:27:28,274
So gorgeous.

403
00:27:36,844 --> 00:27:40,515
So you pretty much created
a flashlight that looks like a...

404
00:27:41,849 --> 00:27:42,849
a wand?

405
00:27:44,431 --> 00:27:45,764
Not ordinary wand.

406
00:27:45,789 --> 00:27:48,481
It has a voice recognition system
installed.

407
00:27:48,523 --> 00:27:50,983
You don’t need to press a button
or flip a switch.

408
00:27:50,984 --> 00:27:52,693
Just say the magic word.

409
00:27:52,694 --> 00:27:55,028
Like this!
It only has five spells available, look...

410
00:27:55,029 --> 00:27:56,614
Can we now focus on the case?

411
00:27:57,490 --> 00:27:59,200
Lights on, please.

412
00:28:01,369 --> 00:28:05,164
I'm just gonna tinker off with my wand.

413
00:28:05,873 --> 00:28:06,873
Leonora!

414
00:28:07,125 --> 00:28:08,167
- Leona!
- Yes?

415
00:28:10,461 --> 00:28:12,714
When you went
near the second victim's body,

416
00:28:13,172 --> 00:28:15,550
did you notice anyone
pricking him on the nape?

417
00:28:15,967 --> 00:28:18,636
Or did you see a needle-like object?

418
00:28:19,262 --> 00:28:20,262
No.

419
00:28:21,347 --> 00:28:23,474
We didn’t have time to check the body.

420
00:28:24,183 --> 00:28:27,395
Well, my team immediately carried him
to the clinic.

421
00:28:28,521 --> 00:28:30,815
So if someone pricked him,

422
00:28:31,566 --> 00:28:33,276
we didn’t notice it.

423
00:28:35,278 --> 00:28:37,529
Who else was with you in the video?

424
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:41,409
Oh, Rowen Ravino and Helios Hontiveros.

425
00:28:41,576 --> 00:28:43,953
They’re also the founders
of the Fellowship.

426
00:28:44,621 --> 00:28:45,621
Okay.

427
00:28:45,997 --> 00:28:48,374
What was their relationship
with the victim?

428
00:28:48,875 --> 00:28:51,043
Sorry, I know this might sound
like a stretch,

429
00:28:51,044 --> 00:28:54,130
but it seems like they weren’t that close.

430
00:28:55,214 --> 00:28:58,259
Usually, if people are friends,

431
00:28:58,885 --> 00:29:01,137
they are all together side by side.

432
00:29:02,013 --> 00:29:04,265
But judging by their body language,

433
00:29:04,766 --> 00:29:06,476
Sylvester was trailing behind.

434
00:29:07,560 --> 00:29:10,188
He isn’t walking ahead. No urgency.

435
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:12,217
Spot on observation!

436
00:29:13,274 --> 00:29:16,944
Is it possible those two
had a motive against Sylvester?

437
00:29:17,642 --> 00:29:19,352
Well, you’re right!

438
00:29:20,198 --> 00:29:22,784
The four founders have always
had disagreements.

439
00:29:23,368 --> 00:29:25,578
So, they’re not that close.

440
00:29:25,870 --> 00:29:30,917
Well, Sylvester wanted stricter selection
for members entering the Fellowship.

441
00:29:31,793 --> 00:29:33,835
Meanwhile, the other three founders

442
00:29:33,836 --> 00:29:37,465
are fine with anyone who’s willing
to pay the membership fee.

443
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:41,502
Some of our applicants
aren’t really fans or readers.

444
00:29:41,844 --> 00:29:44,514
They’re just following the trend
because our club is popular.

445
00:29:45,014 --> 00:29:46,057
In short,

446
00:29:46,474 --> 00:29:49,535
the remaining two founders
will somehow benefit

447
00:29:49,708 --> 00:29:51,293
from their colleague's death.

448
00:29:52,199 --> 00:29:53,659
No more opposition for them.

449
00:29:54,278 --> 00:29:57,281
Is there anyone else who will benefit?

450
00:29:59,821 --> 00:30:03,950
I think the one who will replace
Sylvester as Mage of Earth.

451
00:30:04,742 --> 00:30:05,909
Do you know him?

452
00:30:06,027 --> 00:30:08,196
Yes. Lucius Malvar.

453
00:30:08,538 --> 00:30:12,458
Actually, his appointment will be
announced later at the acquaintance party.

454
00:30:15,085 --> 00:30:16,711
He can be a suspect,

455
00:30:17,848 --> 00:30:19,141
an accomplice,

456
00:30:20,298 --> 00:30:21,298
or a target.

457
00:30:22,350 --> 00:30:23,351
What do you think?

458
00:30:24,637 --> 00:30:25,637
Well...

459
00:30:26,055 --> 00:30:30,810
what we do know is that two
of the four founders are now dead.

460
00:30:31,436 --> 00:30:33,229
And there’s still the possibility

461
00:30:33,396 --> 00:30:36,023
that the killer
is targeting their leaders.

462
00:30:37,316 --> 00:30:40,805
If the culprit is someone who has
a grudge against the founders,

463
00:30:41,570 --> 00:30:43,864
they may need to vet
for more replacements.

464
00:30:45,065 --> 00:30:48,694
If both or either of the founders
drop dead later,

465
00:30:49,351 --> 00:30:51,395
this becomes a serial killing.

466
00:30:57,135 --> 00:30:59,095
What? We're wizards.

467
00:31:30,119 --> 00:31:31,496
Hello, Al?

468
00:31:31,954 --> 00:31:34,540
How are you?
Are you done with your errands?

469
00:31:35,792 --> 00:31:37,335
Yeah, I just finished.

470
00:31:37,502 --> 00:31:42,173
And actually, it was a lunch meeting
with your dad.

471
00:31:42,612 --> 00:31:45,281
What? You had lunch with Papa?

472
00:31:45,760 --> 00:31:47,470
Why didn’t you tell me right away?

473
00:31:48,095 --> 00:31:51,224
Because I knew you’d react like that.

474
00:31:51,724 --> 00:31:53,204
But you don’t have to worry about it,

475
00:31:53,601 --> 00:31:54,852
<i>he was just asking about you.</i>

476
00:31:54,977 --> 00:31:57,396
- Good thing you told me.
- Who are you with? Lorelei?

477
00:31:57,688 --> 00:32:00,273
- Yeah, over there.
- Anyway, Loki and I have figured out.

478
00:32:00,274 --> 00:32:02,025
- How about you?
- That the two murders

479
00:32:02,026 --> 00:32:04,194
are likely connected to a killing spree

480
00:32:04,195 --> 00:32:06,113
<i>targeting the club’s founders.</i>

481
00:32:06,948 --> 00:32:08,783
<i>Many lives are at risk.</i>

482
00:32:08,950 --> 00:32:12,369
That’s why we’re here
at their acquaintance party now.

483
00:32:12,370 --> 00:32:16,958
To investigate and hopefully, to prevent
the killer from striking again.

484
00:32:17,959 --> 00:32:21,587
Okay. Observe those who come into contact
with the potential targets.

485
00:32:21,838 --> 00:32:25,258
And also take note of who shakes hands
with them and who approaches them.

486
00:32:25,550 --> 00:32:28,134
And also those who aren’t too far.

487
00:32:28,135 --> 00:32:32,306
People within about five to ten meters,
something like that.

488
00:32:32,723 --> 00:32:35,101
Five to ten meters? Why?

489
00:32:35,476 --> 00:32:37,603
I did some research about curare.

490
00:32:37,645 --> 00:32:41,761
Indigenous people in South America
dip their arrows or blowgun darts

491
00:32:41,786 --> 00:32:43,955
in curare before hunting their prey.

492
00:32:44,193 --> 00:32:46,404
Are you saying there’s a possibility

493
00:32:46,946 --> 00:32:50,533
the killer didn’t need
to get close to the victims?

494
00:32:51,325 --> 00:32:53,411
<i>Like, the killer used blowgun?</i>

495
00:32:53,995 --> 00:32:57,956
Possible, because even after reviewing
the video you sent,

496
00:32:57,957 --> 00:33:01,002
there’s no sign of any student
carrying that kind of weapon.

497
00:33:01,377 --> 00:33:04,296
It’s either the culprit
isn’t visible in the frame,

498
00:33:04,297 --> 00:33:07,258
or they found a clever way
to conceal the weapon.

499
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,886
But there’s a flaw in that reasoning.

500
00:33:10,678 --> 00:33:12,513
If it really was a blowgun used,

501
00:33:13,222 --> 00:33:15,266
how did it manage to penetrate
the victim’s scarf?

502
00:33:16,005 --> 00:33:18,007
<i>You said in the autopsy report,</i>

503
00:33:18,286 --> 00:33:20,705
there were puncture marks
on their napes, right?

504
00:33:20,933 --> 00:33:22,315
I just realized something.

505
00:33:24,233 --> 00:33:26,319
The scarf he was wearing is thin.

506
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:29,257
A needle can easily pass through it.

507
00:33:30,723 --> 00:33:32,890
Lori! Hey! Come!

508
00:33:32,915 --> 00:33:35,001
Loki and Herschel are looking for you.

509
00:33:35,415 --> 00:33:36,666
Sorry, Al. I have to go.

510
00:33:37,211 --> 00:33:39,172
Okay. Alright.
You and Loki take care, okay?

511
00:33:40,583 --> 00:33:42,043
- Hey, what's up?
- What's up?

512
00:33:42,293 --> 00:33:43,710
Oh, here she is!

513
00:33:43,711 --> 00:33:45,211
Guys, guys. I'm gonna show you, guys.

514
00:33:45,212 --> 00:33:46,880
This is Lorelei Rios.

515
00:33:46,881 --> 00:33:50,759
She’s also the vice president
of the FOTW at Clark U.

516
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:53,716
She’s also a House of Life
like you, Helios.

517
00:33:53,741 --> 00:33:56,285
- Come on, come on.
- I'm Helios Hontiveros, by the way.

518
00:33:56,515 --> 00:34:00,494
Always pleased
to meet a fellow House of Life.

519
00:34:00,519 --> 00:34:01,479
Yeah.

520
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:03,355
And I am Rowen Ravino.

521
00:34:03,356 --> 00:34:04,648
House of Sky.

522
00:34:04,851 --> 00:34:06,561
What an honor to make your acquaintance.

523
00:34:06,817 --> 00:34:09,070
- It's nice to meet you both.
- Just enjoy the party.

524
00:34:09,153 --> 00:34:10,196
You guys wanna go with us?

525
00:34:10,488 --> 00:34:11,905
- Sure.
- Oh, okay.

526
00:34:11,906 --> 00:34:13,657
- Yeah.
- See you. Bye, bestie.

527
00:34:13,836 --> 00:34:14,920
Miss you!

528
00:34:23,417 --> 00:34:27,296
So, what did your childhood friend say
during your phone call outside?

529
00:34:28,047 --> 00:34:31,759
Wait. How did you know Alistair
was the one I was talking to?

530
00:34:32,843 --> 00:34:35,470
Well, it could be your aunt,

531
00:34:35,471 --> 00:34:37,306
but she'll message you first
before calling.

532
00:34:37,640 --> 00:34:38,641
Unless it's urgent.

533
00:34:39,183 --> 00:34:41,978
It could be your father,
but you're not fond of him.

534
00:34:42,478 --> 00:34:46,440
So, your conversation won't probably last
for more than 30 seconds.

535
00:34:47,024 --> 00:34:49,026
It could be any of your classmates,

536
00:34:49,777 --> 00:34:51,112
but today's a weekend,

537
00:34:51,445 --> 00:34:53,125
so, you're not required
to take their call.

538
00:34:54,615 --> 00:34:56,701
So, that leaves, Alistair,

539
00:34:57,702 --> 00:35:00,788
the only one who can make you stay
on the line for five minutes.

540
00:35:01,414 --> 00:35:02,248
Sssh!

541
00:35:02,248 --> 00:35:03,248
Sorry.

542
00:35:05,334 --> 00:35:07,527
Well, I’m impressed.

543
00:35:08,013 --> 00:35:10,432
But anyway, speaking of Alistair,

544
00:35:10,977 --> 00:35:12,562
he told me he thinks

545
00:35:13,259 --> 00:35:17,013
the culprit probably used a blowgun
or something to that effect

546
00:35:17,304 --> 00:35:20,224
to shoot a poison-laced needle
at the victims.

547
00:35:20,474 --> 00:35:23,810
So, basically, the suspect didn’t need
to get close to the victims

548
00:35:23,811 --> 00:35:24,937
to prick them with a needle.

549
00:35:26,105 --> 00:35:27,773
I've arrived at the same theory.

550
00:35:28,649 --> 00:35:30,400
And this case reminds me

551
00:35:30,401 --> 00:35:33,487
of the Sherlock Holmes Novel,
The Sign of Four.

552
00:35:35,281 --> 00:35:37,074
Where the murderer used a blow pipe

553
00:35:37,658 --> 00:35:41,120
to shoot at the victim
with a poisoned dart.

554
00:35:42,621 --> 00:35:44,831
Dear, Fellows of the Wands!

555
00:35:44,832 --> 00:35:48,001
Please rise and prepare your wands!

556
00:35:48,188 --> 00:35:50,899
The program is about to begin!

557
00:35:55,426 --> 00:35:56,426
Look...

558
00:35:56,793 --> 00:35:58,795
she's gonna ask us to do something stupid.

559
00:35:59,597 --> 00:36:00,597
In three,

560
00:36:01,182 --> 00:36:02,182
two,

561
00:36:02,558 --> 00:36:03,451
one…

562
00:36:03,476 --> 00:36:07,997
Raise your wands and illuminate
the hall with your magic.

563
00:36:08,022 --> 00:36:09,957
On the count of three!

564
00:36:09,982 --> 00:36:13,276
One, two, three!

565
00:36:13,277 --> 00:36:16,402
Ilumino Magna!

566
00:36:18,199 --> 00:36:21,410
- Welcome to the grand acquiantance party.
- Ilumino Magna.

567
00:36:21,837 --> 00:36:24,423
Today is a special day.

568
00:36:25,956 --> 00:36:26,956
Hey!

569
00:36:27,416 --> 00:36:28,501
Is there a problem?

570
00:36:29,877 --> 00:36:32,755
I think something’s
just wrong with the wire.

571
00:36:33,380 --> 00:36:35,715
Probably about the voice
recognition something.

572
00:36:35,716 --> 00:36:37,843
But, don’t worry. I’ll fix it later.

573
00:36:38,052 --> 00:36:39,052
It’s alright!

574
00:36:46,387 --> 00:36:47,387
<i>Their wands…</i>

575
00:36:47,853 --> 00:36:50,064
<i>is this related
to the wands that they have?</i>

576
00:37:09,792 --> 00:37:13,546
To the new members
of the Fellowship, welcome!

577
00:37:14,046 --> 00:37:17,049
To the old members, welcome back!

578
00:37:21,679 --> 00:37:24,640
Before we officially begin
our acquaintance party,

579
00:37:25,141 --> 00:37:27,976
let us offer a moment of silence

580
00:37:27,977 --> 00:37:31,438
for the two fallen founders
of the Fellowship.

581
00:37:37,570 --> 00:37:40,865
In light of the untimely passing
of our colleagues,

582
00:37:41,824 --> 00:37:44,743
we, the remaining founders,

583
00:37:45,077 --> 00:37:48,079
have chosen the right person

584
00:37:48,080 --> 00:37:50,040
to lead the House of Earth.

585
00:37:50,708 --> 00:37:53,252
Wizards, a round of applause

586
00:37:53,961 --> 00:37:57,506
for Lucius Malvar, the new Mage of Earth.

587
00:37:57,798 --> 00:37:59,632
Lucius! Lucius!

588
00:37:59,633 --> 00:38:02,135
Lucius! Lucius! Lucius!

589
00:38:02,136 --> 00:38:04,721
Lucius! Lucius! Lucius!

590
00:38:04,722 --> 00:38:06,515
Lucius! Lucius!

591
00:38:08,225 --> 00:38:10,019
In the name of the Houses...

592
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:14,899
He's looking at his phone.

593
00:38:15,399 --> 00:38:17,234
And that’s the Havre K'davra message.

594
00:38:21,363 --> 00:38:23,949
- Rowen! Rowen!
- Hey!

595
00:38:24,345 --> 00:38:25,638
- Rowen!
- Call the police!

596
00:38:25,743 --> 00:38:27,411
Hershey! Lock the venue!

597
00:38:27,494 --> 00:38:29,389
- No one gets out! Lock the door!
- No one gets out!

598
00:38:29,515 --> 00:38:30,599
Rowen, are you okay?

599
00:38:31,165 --> 00:38:33,626
Rowen, come on! Rowen!

600
00:38:33,751 --> 00:38:35,276
- Hey! Don’t touch him!
- Rowen!

601
00:38:40,966 --> 00:38:42,009
Is there a pulse?

602
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:47,680
He's gone.

603
00:38:49,600 --> 00:38:50,976
Who are you two, really?

604
00:38:51,477 --> 00:38:53,687
Why won’t you let us
get close to Rowen’s body?

605
00:38:54,438 --> 00:38:56,112
And now you’re right beside him?

606
00:38:59,568 --> 00:39:00,568
Okay.

607
00:39:01,237 --> 00:39:02,237
We lied.

608
00:39:03,072 --> 00:39:04,573
We’re not Wizardly fans.

609
00:39:05,074 --> 00:39:07,243
We're detectives hired to investigate

610
00:39:07,660 --> 00:39:09,662
the murders of your two founders.

611
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:11,163
And now, three.

612
00:39:12,403 --> 00:39:14,321
Hershey, did you bring your thing?

613
00:39:31,475 --> 00:39:32,475
Gotcha!

614
00:39:32,726 --> 00:39:35,104
No one gets out, everyone!

615
00:39:35,603 --> 00:39:37,897
Please stay calm until the police arrive.

616
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:39,692
I’ll call the cops.

617
00:39:40,393 --> 00:39:42,793
- How? We never even got close to him.
- How did this happen?

618
00:39:43,354 --> 00:39:46,357
You saw the distance
between us and him, right?

619
00:39:47,324 --> 00:39:49,702
There's no need
for any close physical contact.

620
00:39:50,369 --> 00:39:53,329
All you need
is a cleverly disguised contraption

621
00:39:53,330 --> 00:39:55,082
that can shoot this needle.

622
00:39:55,624 --> 00:39:57,918
Something that won’t raise suspicion.

623
00:39:59,249 --> 00:40:00,667
Like this wand…

624
00:40:01,839 --> 00:40:03,382
it could also be hiding a blowgun.

625
00:40:04,216 --> 00:40:05,592
No one would suspect

626
00:40:06,135 --> 00:40:09,179
that this fake wand can kill.

627
00:40:09,763 --> 00:40:10,763
Correct!

628
00:40:11,307 --> 00:40:12,975
Now it's the part where we apply

629
00:40:13,501 --> 00:40:15,419
the process of elimination.

630
00:40:18,022 --> 00:40:19,606
You were on the stage with Rowen,

631
00:40:20,357 --> 00:40:21,775
a few steps away from him.

632
00:40:22,552 --> 00:40:23,719
He's an easy target.

633
00:40:24,785 --> 00:40:27,371
But the puncture mark
is on the right side of his neck.

634
00:40:27,948 --> 00:40:30,034
Helios is on his left side

635
00:40:30,617 --> 00:40:32,745
while Lucius is kneeling.

636
00:40:33,971 --> 00:40:35,639
So if he’s the one who did it,

637
00:40:35,819 --> 00:40:37,279
we’ll know immediately.

638
00:40:38,751 --> 00:40:40,294
Maybe it's someone from the crowd,

639
00:40:40,961 --> 00:40:43,797
someone who's a meter
or two away from Rowen,

640
00:40:44,938 --> 00:40:46,356
standing within the range

641
00:40:46,425 --> 00:40:50,220
needed to shoot
the poison-laced needle at the victim.

642
00:40:52,167 --> 00:40:53,168
And among them,

643
00:40:53,807 --> 00:40:56,352
who is smart enough to modify the wand

644
00:40:57,135 --> 00:40:58,470
into a murder weapon?

645
00:40:59,396 --> 00:41:00,439
Who among them

646
00:41:00,898 --> 00:41:02,900
appeared in the CCTV footage?

647
00:41:08,419 --> 00:41:09,419
Leona?

648
00:41:17,039 --> 00:41:19,224
Hey! Is there a problem?

649
00:41:19,249 --> 00:41:22,127
I think something’s wrong with the wire.

650
00:41:22,378 --> 00:41:23,921
Don’t worry, I’ll fix it later.

651
00:41:25,214 --> 00:41:26,214
You.

652
00:41:27,299 --> 00:41:28,967
You're in the perfect position…

653
00:41:29,051 --> 00:41:30,511
to shoot at the victim.

654
00:42:13,137 --> 00:42:15,180
Do you mind if Hershey
inspects your wand?

655
00:42:15,915 --> 00:42:18,334
This will instantly prove your innocence.

656
00:42:21,770 --> 00:42:23,730
You shouldn’t have gotten
involved in this.

657
00:42:25,899 --> 00:42:28,995
But I couldn’t have done this
without them!

658
00:42:31,565 --> 00:42:32,858
Those four...

659
00:42:34,366 --> 00:42:37,003
are the reason Emma died!

660
00:42:41,375 --> 00:42:43,502
They were the first to kill!

661
00:42:48,197 --> 00:42:49,573
<i>Those four...</i>

662
00:42:50,048 --> 00:42:54,136
<i>the idea to start the Wizardly fan club
didn’t come from them.</i>

663
00:42:54,636 --> 00:42:56,388
<i>It came from Emma.</i>

664
00:43:03,979 --> 00:43:05,689
<i>They stole her idea,</i>

665
00:43:06,398 --> 00:43:08,734
<i>made it look like it was theirs,</i>

666
00:43:10,402 --> 00:43:12,738
<i>and then banned her from joining.</i>

667
00:43:14,531 --> 00:43:17,033
<i>They were just going to use Emma's idea</i>

668
00:43:17,034 --> 00:43:21,663
<i>to scam money from membership fees
and Wizardly item sales.</i>

669
00:43:25,626 --> 00:43:27,669
<i>She tried to defend herself.</i>

670
00:43:27,878 --> 00:43:30,338
<i>She insisted they stole her idea,</i>

671
00:43:30,339 --> 00:43:33,300
<i>but those four made her look like a liar.</i>

672
00:43:36,470 --> 00:43:37,262
<i>And then she was bullied</i>

673
00:43:37,263 --> 00:43:40,724
<i>by the Fellowship’s die-hard members
like a cult!</i>

674
00:43:45,229 --> 00:43:48,065
<i>Emma’s mental health deteriorated</i>

675
00:43:49,650 --> 00:43:52,738
<i>until she finally ended her own life.</i>

676
00:44:00,112 --> 00:44:03,866
<i>I transferred to Chivalry
just to join the Fellowship.</i>

677
00:44:07,130 --> 00:44:10,133
<i>I promised I would get revenge
on those guys.</i>

678
00:44:10,922 --> 00:44:15,363
<i>I won’t stop until the same thing
that happened to Emma happens to them.</i>

679
00:44:39,032 --> 00:44:42,828
I’d rather be gone than end up in prison!

680
00:44:43,421 --> 00:44:46,007
I’ve avenged my friend…

681
00:44:47,013 --> 00:44:48,598
My only friend!

682
00:44:50,794 --> 00:44:51,794
Leona, don't!

683
00:44:51,920 --> 00:44:52,920
Stupere!

684
00:44:54,464 --> 00:44:55,464
Oh, my gosh.

685
00:44:56,508 --> 00:44:58,718
Don't worry,
"Stupere" is just a voice command

686
00:44:58,719 --> 00:45:01,930
that can generate high power voltage
with low amperage charge.

687
00:45:02,264 --> 00:45:03,264
Let's go, man.

688
00:45:03,564 --> 00:45:04,773
Come on. Move.

689
00:45:05,601 --> 00:45:06,601
It was her!

690
00:45:06,809 --> 00:45:07,977
She’s the one who killed!

691
00:45:27,689 --> 00:45:30,191
Guys, thank you for your help.

692
00:45:30,334 --> 00:45:32,543
It’s sad, that all this time,

693
00:45:32,544 --> 00:45:36,965
the person closest to me at school
was the killer.

694
00:45:38,038 --> 00:45:39,359
What a waste of genius.

695
00:45:39,384 --> 00:45:42,887
But Helios and some Fellowship officers
are still being investigated

696
00:45:42,888 --> 00:45:46,266
for corruption on high registration fees
and overpricing substandard items.

697
00:45:47,434 --> 00:45:50,270
If they hadn’t deceived Emma,
this wouldn’t have happened.

698
00:45:51,647 --> 00:45:53,648
Loki, Lori,

699
00:45:53,649 --> 00:45:54,876
I hope to see you again.

700
00:45:54,901 --> 00:45:57,445
But under better circumstances, I hope.

701
00:45:57,778 --> 00:45:59,863
- Be careful, Herschel.
- Thank you.

702
00:45:59,946 --> 00:46:00,989
Thank you, Hershey.

703
00:46:08,580 --> 00:46:11,625
The founders were wrong
in what they did to Leona’s friend.

704
00:46:12,125 --> 00:46:13,835
But killing is even more wrong.

705
00:46:15,545 --> 00:46:20,342
Stealing ideas and deceiving others
brings nothing good.

706
00:46:21,468 --> 00:46:24,513
But revenge brings even less good.

707
00:46:25,472 --> 00:46:26,472
Right?

708
00:46:30,519 --> 00:46:31,645
Yeah.

709
00:46:42,823 --> 00:46:45,283
When did you find out
Leona was the culprit?

710
00:46:46,076 --> 00:46:47,160
Was it at the party?

711
00:46:49,550 --> 00:46:50,550
In their lab,

712
00:46:51,039 --> 00:46:55,252
<i>right after I realized that the killer
had concealed the murder weapon</i>

713
00:46:55,669 --> 00:46:59,506
<i>into an object that would not raise
any suspicions.</i>

714
00:47:00,632 --> 00:47:03,552
Only her and Herschel
could make a weapon like that.

715
00:47:05,303 --> 00:47:07,681
And Herschel isn’t in the footage,

716
00:47:08,477 --> 00:47:10,354
and he has a strong alibi.

717
00:47:11,248 --> 00:47:12,499
So, it only leaves to...

718
00:47:13,353 --> 00:47:14,353
Leona.

719
00:47:16,523 --> 00:47:18,859
But why didn’t you tell me right away?

720
00:47:19,776 --> 00:47:23,155
If we were to accuse an innocent
looking girl who was kind to us...

721
00:47:24,114 --> 00:47:26,867
surely, you would be affected.

722
00:47:28,034 --> 00:47:30,036
And I needed you to act naturally,

723
00:47:31,204 --> 00:47:33,749
or she would suspect
that we were on to something.

724
00:47:36,931 --> 00:47:38,891
I still can’t believe it.

725
00:47:40,255 --> 00:47:41,381
It’s such a shame.

726
00:47:59,741 --> 00:48:00,951
Is there a problem?

727
00:48:03,744 --> 00:48:05,245
Somebody broke into our unit.

728
00:48:09,002 --> 00:48:10,002
What?

729
00:48:12,788 --> 00:48:16,666
Before leaving, I put this
between the door and its frame.

730
00:48:17,635 --> 00:48:19,095
If anyone opened the door,

731
00:48:19,961 --> 00:48:21,961
this piece of paper
would have fallen to the floor.

732
00:48:23,818 --> 00:48:25,027
Which means...

733
00:48:26,092 --> 00:48:27,928
someone was inside before us.

734
00:48:31,375 --> 00:48:32,668
Were we robbed?

735
00:48:38,142 --> 00:48:39,413
Shit!

736
00:48:39,439 --> 00:48:40,440
Shit!

737
00:48:40,816 --> 00:48:41,816
Shit!

738
00:48:45,195 --> 00:48:46,195
Where is it?

739
00:48:47,364 --> 00:48:48,364
Shit.

740
00:48:53,537 --> 00:48:54,538
Where is it?

741
00:48:59,376 --> 00:49:01,545
It doesn’t look like
any of my things were touched.

742
00:49:03,129 --> 00:49:04,339
My laptop is gone.

743
00:49:06,466 --> 00:49:08,218
The one containing Pandora’s box.

744
00:49:15,809 --> 00:49:17,352
Did someone break into your apartment?

745
00:49:18,478 --> 00:49:20,038
Do you have any clues about who did it?

746
00:49:21,273 --> 00:49:25,485
Tita Martha said she didn’t notice
anyone suspicious entering the apartment.

747
00:49:26,143 --> 00:49:28,774
We also asked the tenants
in the other units,

748
00:49:28,807 --> 00:49:32,267
but they didn’t notice
anything unusual either.

749
00:49:32,617 --> 00:49:35,202
There are no CCTV cameras
on each floor either.

750
00:49:35,203 --> 00:49:36,579
So until now,

751
00:49:36,580 --> 00:49:40,208
we still don’t have a clue on who did this
and what they looked like.

752
00:49:40,542 --> 00:49:42,627
And only Loki’s laptop was taken?

753
00:49:42,794 --> 00:49:45,505
The one who took it
definitely knew its contents.

754
00:49:46,006 --> 00:49:47,431
Wait, what was in it?

755
00:49:47,924 --> 00:49:50,009
Well, let’s just say,

756
00:49:50,010 --> 00:49:51,927
that the laptop contains files

757
00:49:51,928 --> 00:49:54,471
that Loki could use in the future

758
00:49:54,472 --> 00:49:56,308
to turn the situation in his favor.

759
00:49:56,892 --> 00:49:57,892
But anyway,

760
00:49:58,310 --> 00:50:00,770
I think Loki already has a plan for that.

761
00:50:03,273 --> 00:50:04,482
Lori, on a different note,

762
00:50:04,941 --> 00:50:07,402
Saint Barths’ cultural fest is coming up.

763
00:50:07,569 --> 00:50:10,881
And I talked to Lionel before I left.

764
00:50:10,991 --> 00:50:14,577
He said we’re welcome to go if we want.

765
00:50:15,577 --> 00:50:16,578
Do you want?

766
00:50:20,832 --> 00:50:22,000
Lori, look...

767
00:50:22,918 --> 00:50:24,669
if you don't like, you don’t have to go.

768
00:50:26,225 --> 00:50:28,477
There’s still a long week
before the event.

769
00:50:29,548 --> 00:50:30,716
Think about it.

770
00:50:31,902 --> 00:50:34,321
Okay. I'll let you know.

771
00:50:34,930 --> 00:50:36,013
If there’s anything I can do

772
00:50:36,014 --> 00:50:38,600
to ease your negative feelings
about our school,

773
00:50:38,642 --> 00:50:39,643
I’ll do it.

774
00:50:40,518 --> 00:50:43,688
If only I had a magic wand
and could cast a spell,

775
00:50:44,272 --> 00:50:45,272
I’d do it.

776
00:51:00,455 --> 00:51:03,124
“Quod Erat Demonstrandum.”

777
00:51:08,964 --> 00:51:10,757
"Which was to be demonstrated."

778
00:51:11,132 --> 00:51:12,717
You can Google what that means.

779
00:51:13,843 --> 00:51:14,970
Because it’s in Latin,

780
00:51:15,512 --> 00:51:18,098
it sounds like an ancient spell.

781
00:51:19,057 --> 00:51:21,034
It feels like there’s something magical

782
00:51:21,059 --> 00:51:22,477
whenever a case gets solved.

783
00:51:32,612 --> 00:51:33,612
Loki?

784
00:51:34,656 --> 00:51:36,241
Is your suspension lifted now?

785
00:51:40,996 --> 00:51:42,831
I wouldn't be here
if it wasn't the case.

786
00:51:44,874 --> 00:51:47,127
Oh, Jamie, meet our newest member,

787
00:51:47,877 --> 00:51:49,212
Lorelei's childhood friend..

788
00:51:50,171 --> 00:51:51,171
Al...

789
00:51:51,506 --> 00:51:52,506
Alexander.

790
00:51:52,924 --> 00:51:53,925
Alistair!

791
00:51:55,634 --> 00:51:56,718
Nice meeting you!

792
00:51:57,887 --> 00:51:59,221
OMG!

793
00:51:59,222 --> 00:52:02,017
This is so exciting, there are four
of us in the Q.E.D. Club now!

794
00:52:02,826 --> 00:52:03,909
You know what,

795
00:52:03,934 --> 00:52:07,020
we should hold a party
to celebrate Loki’s return.

796
00:52:07,272 --> 00:52:11,026
And it’s also a welcome party
for Alistair.

797
00:52:11,192 --> 00:52:12,192
Right?

798
00:52:12,736 --> 00:52:14,361
Instead of holding a party,

799
00:52:14,362 --> 00:52:16,489
we must focus on solving cases.

800
00:52:17,824 --> 00:52:20,326
Once the students find out
the Q.E.D. Club is back,

801
00:52:20,910 --> 00:52:22,454
our clients will come rushing in.

802
00:52:22,954 --> 00:52:24,289
And we should be ready.

803
00:52:24,998 --> 00:52:29,376
Come on, Loki! It’s just this once, please?

804
00:52:29,501 --> 00:52:31,670
You know what,
let’s just enjoy your return.

805
00:52:32,092 --> 00:52:34,011
We should have some fun!

806
00:52:34,649 --> 00:52:36,276
- Loki, please.
- Careful.

807
00:52:36,480 --> 00:52:39,524
Her facial expression changed
when we entered the room.

808
00:52:39,679 --> 00:52:40,971
She gave me a nasty look,

809
00:52:40,972 --> 00:52:43,099
but when she introduced herself,
she was all smiles.

810
00:52:43,433 --> 00:52:45,976
You know, we’re complete.
We’re only complete now.

811
00:52:45,977 --> 00:52:47,996
There's more to her than meets the eye.

812
00:52:48,163 --> 00:52:49,497
Just be careful, okay?

813
00:52:49,522 --> 00:52:51,900
Let's also welcome Alistair.

814
00:52:53,026 --> 00:52:54,110
Please.

815
00:52:54,860 --> 00:52:55,861
Okay. Fine!

816
00:52:56,821 --> 00:52:57,864
Let’s have it your way.

817
00:52:58,323 --> 00:53:00,408
Just don't ask me to buy
you food and drinks,

818
00:53:00,867 --> 00:53:02,951
since it’s your idea to have the party.

819
00:53:02,952 --> 00:53:04,871
No problem! We got that.

820
00:53:07,528 --> 00:53:09,280
What should we order?

821
00:53:10,376 --> 00:53:13,170
<i>And just when we though that finally</i>

822
00:53:13,171 --> 00:53:15,590
<i>we had a reason to celebrate
our small wins...</i>

823
00:53:16,174 --> 00:53:19,928
<i>we suddenly found out that the mystery
still hadn't been solved.</i>

824
00:53:55,421 --> 00:53:56,589
<i>That man…</i>

825
00:53:58,466 --> 00:53:59,801
<i>whatever his real name is...</i>

826
00:54:01,067 --> 00:54:02,402
<i>he’s the one behind.</i>

827
00:54:03,971 --> 00:54:05,639
<i>Why is M doing this?</i>

828
00:54:06,307 --> 00:54:09,644
<i>This Moriarty likes to play games.</i>

829
00:54:10,298 --> 00:54:11,437
<i>He’s everywhere.</i>

830
00:54:12,105 --> 00:54:15,608
<i>He's got eyes and ears, everywhere.</i>

831
00:54:16,317 --> 00:54:18,820
<i>You don’t know
what the Q.E.D. Club means to me.</i>

832
00:54:19,946 --> 00:54:21,488
<i>I’m able to help people</i>

833
00:54:21,489 --> 00:54:23,449
<i>by bringing bad people to justice.</i>

834
00:54:24,450 --> 00:54:27,370
<i>Even if it’s hard,
I’ll fight for this club.</i>

835
00:54:27,996 --> 00:54:31,291
<i>We need to stand together
and fight for this.</i>

836
00:54:31,624 --> 00:54:34,085
<i>And strive to uncover the truth.</i>

837
00:54:35,220 --> 00:54:36,471
I’m Stein Alberts.

838
00:54:36,963 --> 00:54:38,882
I am Moriarty.

839
00:54:40,675 --> 00:54:42,677
<i>No one can stop us.</i>

840
00:54:44,012 --> 00:54:45,430
The game has just begun.

841
00:54:51,923 --> 00:54:54,551
<i>Moriarty is back.</i>

